12/09/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi organised a meeting on Tuesday (September 11th) with Prime Minister Sali Berisha, leader of the Democratic Party, and Tirana Mayor Edi Rama, leader of the opposition Socialist Party, to discuss the future of the capital. 
They agreed both the city and central governments must co-operate to improve Tirana's infrastructure plan and bring it up to international standards. 
(Shekulli, Kohajone, Shqip - 12/09/07; Balkanweb, Top-Channel, Albanian President web site - 11/09/07)
